---
title: Venison Steak & Thyme-Pepper Sauce with Roasted Veggies & Nutty Baby Broccoli
description: There’s something eternally comforting about the aroma of a peppery thyme sauce. Completely mouth-watering to say the least. Drizzled over tender seared venison steak with a side of greens and toasted almonds, it’s time for pub-style steak and potatoes to move over; there’s a new and completely luxe contender in town.

*This recipe is under 650kcal per serving and under 40g carbohydrates per serving.*
